The paper discusses privacy preservation in high-dimensional data sets, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). It also addresses the issue of privacy attacks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper proposes a method for data anonymization, which involves information theory and statistical analysis, indicating a connection to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The approach also involves decomposition of data into subsets, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses mutual information as a criterion for the decomposition process, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
